{"type":"message","id":"4ae61c60","parentId":"fe88b128","timestamp":"2026-04-02T10:30:00.058Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:321d856c-eb47-44d0-a1de-24fd64d31f4f 盘后复盘+邮件报告] 执行每日盘后复盘流程：\n1. SCP 从云服务器拉取 E:/Quant/Datas/daily_result.json 和 E:/Quant/Datas/positions.json\n2. 读今天的 plan.json（对比预测 vs 实际）\n3. 读历史报告索引 _index.json（防止重复犯错）\n4. 量化团队全員复盘：\n   - 今日盈亏是多少？每只股票表现如何？\n   - 哪些因子对了？哪些因子错了？\n5. **因子有效性追踪**（重要）：\n   - 读 strategies/reports/factor_tracking.json\n   - 对比今日每只股票的选股因子（PE/PB分位、机构资金流向、ROE趋势、换手率异动等）\n   - 判断哪些因子与正收益相关、哪些因子失效\n   - 更新 factor_tracking.json：更新各因子的 days_above/days_below、avg_return_when_signal、hit_rate，追加 notes\n   - 保存更新后的 factor_tracking.json\n   - 在报告中输出因子有效性排行榜：最有效因子 TOP3 + 最失效因子 TOP3\n6. **新闻回溯**（个股异常时触发）：\n   - 如果某只持仓股当日涨跌幅 > 5% 或触发止损/止盈，搜索该股票当日相关新闻\n   - 用 web_search 搜索 \"股票代码/名称 + 新闻\" 和所属行业相关新闻\n   - 分析新闻是否为涨跌原因，记录到因子追踪的 notes 中\n   - 如果是突发利空/利好导致止损/止盈，标注为「新闻驱动」类型\n7. 生成 Markdown 复盘报告，包含：\n   - 今日盈亏总览\n   - 个股表现明细（异常个股附新闻回溯）\n   - 因子有效性分析（排行榜）\n   - 教训总结（对比 _index.json 防重复）\n   - 明日关注点\n8. 用 Gmail SMTP 发邮件到 l1cheeyuan@163.com\n   - 发件箱: yuanlynch@gmail.com\n   - App Password: jsnjyjwpavymplev\n   - SMTP: smtp.gmail.com:587, STARTTLS\n   - 参考脚本: /Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace/send_morning_report.py\nCurrent time: Thursday, April 2nd, 2026 — 18:30 (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-04-02 10:30 UTC\n\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself."}],"timestamp":1775125800058}}
{"type":"message","id":"8479007c","parentId":"4ae61c60","timestamp":"2026-04-02T10:30:28.508Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"\nLooking at this request, it's a cron job that needs to execute a daily post-market复盘 (post-market review) with email reporting. The task involves:\n\n1. SCP from cloud server to get daily_result.json and positions.json\n2. Read today's plan.json and historical report index\n3. Quant team review of profit/loss and stock performance\n4. Factor effectiveness tracking \n5. News retrospection if stocks move >5%\n6. Generate Markdown review report\n7. Send email to l1cheeyuan@163.com\n\nThis is clearly a quant trading workflow and the user wants me to execute the cron job. I should use the skills that are relevant for this quant workflow.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I can see several relevant ones:\n- `backtest-expert` for backtesting\n- `financial-calculator` for financial calculations  \n- `market-analysis` for analyzing markets\n- `portfolio-manager` for portfolio analysis\n- `tavily-search` for web search/news\n- Various China stock analysis skills\n\nBut looking more specifically at the AGENTS.md and SOUL.md files, this user \"柴荣\" (Chai Rong) has a very specific workflow and set of tools defined. He uses specific data fetchers and has a structured approach.\n\nLet me start by following the steps outlined:\n\n1. First, I need to SCP the files from the cloud server\n2. Read the plan.json and other files\n3. Analyze the data \n4. Do factor tracking analysis\n5. News search if needed\n6. Generate report\n7. Send email\n\nLet me start step by step.\n\nFor SCP, I'll use the exec command with paramiko approach as mentioned in TOOLS.md.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n<thinking>\nThis is a cron job for daily post-market review (复盘). The user wants me to execute a complete quant trading workflow. Looking at the context, I'm \"柴荣\" (Chai Rong), Lynch's chief quant executive, with specific tools and workflows defined.\n\nThe task requires:\n1. SCP files from cloud server\n2. Read plan.json and historical data\n3. Analyze P&L and stock performance  \n4. Factor effectiveness tracking\n5. News retrospection for big movers\n6. Generate markdown report\n7. Send email\n\nI need to follow the specific quant workflow outlined in the context files. Let me start with step 1 - SCP from cloud server.\n</thinking>\n\nI'll execute the daily post-market review workflow as specified. Let me start by pulling the data from the cloud server.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3f7bd679ad56468da13041f0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"uv run python -c \"\nimport paramiko\nimport json\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Load credentials from environment\nssh_password = os.getenv('SSH_PASSWORD')\nif not ssh_password:\n    print('SSH_PASSWORD environment variable not found')\n    exit(1)\n\n# Connect to cloud server\nssh = paramiko.SSHClient()\nssh.set_missing_host_key_policy(paramiko.AutoAddPolicy())\nssh.connect('118.89.118.199', username='Administrator', password=ssh_password)\n\n# Create local data directory\ndata_dir = Path('data/daily')\ndata_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n# SCP files from cloud server\ndef scp_file(remote_path, local_path):\n    try:\n        sftp = ssh.open_sftp()\n        sftp.get(remote_path, local_path)\n        sftp.close()\n        print(f'Successfully copied {remote_path} to {local_path}')\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f'Error copying {remote_path}: {e}')\n\n# Copy daily result and positions files\nscp_file('E:/Quant/Datas/daily_result.json', str(data_dir / 'daily_result.json'))\nscp_file('E:/Quant/Datas/positions.json', str(data_dir / 'positions.json'))\n\nssh.close()\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-customb2","model":"glm-5-turbo","usage":{"input":33059,"output":800,"cacheRead":8062,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41921,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cache